Keep your Nukes Hot</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=loganwolfxev>LoganwolfXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/03 12:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wich is more important, Mana focus Or HP focus?</span><hr size=1> I would dump your points into Intelligence if you are not planning to get into a major raiding guild.<br>
<br>
If you are like myself, and like to just enjoy the game with a guild of friends, go for intelligence.  It is easy for a casual gamer to get max Intelligence in a few choice slots if you max out your Intelligence at creation.  You will also have a few slots left open for pure hit point items.<br>
<br>
If you plan on joining a raiding guild, it does not matter what you spend your points on.  All the uber drops have like Int +20, Sta +20, Mana +125, HP +125, for every slot. <p>Loganwolf 65 Wizard<br>
<br>
http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=626524</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=loganwolfxev>LoganwolfXev</A> at: 5/22/03 12:22:45 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dephtondisgustipated>Dephton Disgustipated</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/03 6:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wich is more important, Mana focus Or HP focus?</span><hr size=1> personally i think there is more benefit with INT.  at level 65, you get 2.4 hp/stamina, and approx 5mana/int.  this makes those int points double the value imo.  Also, having the higher base int lets you get items that dont neccessarily have to have a ton of int on em.  I didn't know the min max of stats when i made my cahracter, so i went 25int/5wis i think.  if i redid it as an erudite, i would have went 25int 5sta.  im currently capped on int with aa, and im capped on stamina when buffed. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.disgustipated-inc.com/files/sig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Dephton Disgustipated<br>
65 Erudite Arcanist of Solusek Ro<br>
Jade Dragon, Xegony</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=veladorn>Veladorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>I have needs too!</span><br>  Posts: 1307<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/03 7:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wich is more important, Mana focus Or HP focus?</span><hr size=1> INT is always better for a wizard at any level.  I'm shocked there is even a debate about this.<br>
<br>
Aside from more mana, int also helps your overall casting abilities.<br>
<br>
As for maxing your int out at 65..with AAs the INT cap is at 355, it takes a tremendous amount of gear to reach over 355 INT.  Most wizards won't ever reach it and those that do have spent RL years obtaining it, years that could of  benefited from more INT at birth.<br>
<br>
As a wizard INT &gt; HP always.  To think otherwise is heresy!<br>
<br>
