<br>
As a side note, if you make an erudite but the other 5 points into agi or you will have ugly ac penalty. Yes, I know ac is not the most important stat for a wizard. But, why not avoid unneeded pain? <p>-- <br>
Yyidth of the Rathe (lvl 62 wizard)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=delfontes>Delfontes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/03 9:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wich is more important, Mana focus Or HP focus?</span><hr size=1> I think it depends on how &quot;twinked&quot; you are. <br>
<br>
If you can afford to get to 255 int either way, I'd go with stamina.  Currently I would have 281 (I think) unbuffed int, with Kei 306....  my max is still 255.<br>
<br>
Once I have my epic, that is 10 more points...<br>
<br>
My equipment isn't even near uber, and I am in the process of switching items out for more sta/hps/mana and less Int.<br>
<br>
By the time you are lvl 65 with enough AA's to get to 355, you'll be able to achieve it either way. At least that has been my experience with wizards/mages I know with that many AA's. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izelin>Izelin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/03 9:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wich is more important, Mana focus Or HP focus?</span><hr size=1> Its more important to spell which correctly :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draglin>Draglin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/03 10:03 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wich is more important, Mana focus Or HP focus?</span><hr size=1> If your a shaman then I could understand the question since mana and hp are tied together for them after level 24 and their first canni spell.  <br>
